VE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_6Nuh111TwZBlXlGRfoSrgByN", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit library in R.\\n2. Use methylKit::methRead to read the bismark coverage files with the specified parameters.\\n3. Use methylKit::unite to unite the methylation data.\\n4. Save the united methylBase object using saveRDS.\\n5. Write the unite statistics to a TSV file.\\n6. Check if the output file unite_stats.tsv exists.\\n7. Submit the task as done if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (379 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_6Nuh111TwZBlXlGRfoSrgByN"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_zgdAC6yhsjLL69aj3DqsWyGY", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Read the bismark coverage files\\nfile.list <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleC.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleD.bismark.cov')\\ntreatment <- c(0, 0, 1, 1)\\nmk_raw <- methRead(file.list, pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4, treatment=treatment, assembly='mock_v1')\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destra