nt_unmethylated)`.\n\nLoad them with `methylKit::methRead(..., pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4)`,\nusing `treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1)` and assembly `mock_v1`. Then run\n`methylKit::unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)` and save:\n  - `output/mk_united.rds`: the united methylBase object (`saveRDS`).\n  - `output/unite_stats.tsv`: a single-row tab-separated table with columns\n    `n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path` (`write_tsv`).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/unite_stats.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: unite_stats.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_6Nuh111TwZBlXlGRfoSrgByN", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit library in R.\\n2. Use methylKit::methRead to read the bismark coverage files with the specified parameters.\\n3. Use methylKit::unite to unite the methylation data.\\n4. Save the united methylBase object using saveRDS.\\n5. Write the unite statistics to a TSV file.\\n6. Check if the output file unite_stats.tsv exists.\\n7. Submit the task as done if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (379 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_6Nuh111TwZBlXlGRfoSrgByN"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_zgdAC6yhsjLL69aj3DqsWyGY", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Read the bismark coverage files\\nfile.list <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleC.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleD.bismark.cov')\\ntreatment <- c(0, 0, 1, 1)\\nmk_raw <- methRead(file.list, pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4, treatment=treatment, assembly='mock_v1')\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, 'output/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Write unite statistics to a TSV file\\nunite_stats <- data.frame(n_samples=length(mk_united@sample.ids),\\n                          n_sites=length(mk_united@sites),\\n                          min_per_group=1,\\n                          destrand=FALSE,\\n                          use_db=FALSE,\\n                          db_path=NA)\\nwrite.table(unite_stats, 'output/unite_stats.tsv', sep='\\\\t', row.names=FALSE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n    setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018BiocGenerics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    IQR, mad, sd, var, xtabs\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    anyDupli