n": "R expression passed as the argument to `Rscript -e`.", "title": "Code", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["code"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "list_workdir", "description": "List workspace as JSON (bounded depth).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": []}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "write_plan", "description": "Persist a markdown plan to `workspace/.plan.md` (overwrite on rewrite).\n\nUse this at the start of a task and whenever the plan needs revision. The\nplan is not shown automatically on later steps; call check_progress to see\nthe current plan excerpt alongside deliverable state.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"plan": {"description": "Markdown text describing the step-by-step plan (bullet list).", "title": "Plan", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["plan"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "check_progress", "description": "Log a progress note and return a JSON snapshot of deliverables + plan excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `methylkit_unite`\n\n# Real R-task: methylkit_unite\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `fritjoflammers-snakemake-methylanalysis-finish` (family: `methylation`, stage: `mid`, difficulty: `2`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given four per-sample bismark-style coverage files under `input/`:\n`sampleA.bismark.cov`, `sampleB.bismark.cov`, `sampleC.bismark.cov`,\n`sampleD.bismark.cov` \u2014 tab-separated without headers, columns\n`(chrom, start, end, methylation_pct, count_methylated, count_unmethylated)`.\n\nLoad them with `methylKit::methRead(..., pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4)`,\nusing `treatment = c(0, 0, 1, 1)` and assembly `mock_v1`. Then run\n`methylKit::unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)` and save:\n  - `output/mk_united.rds`: the united methylBase object (`saveRDS`).\n  - `output/unite_stats.tsv`: a single-row tab-separated table with columns\n    `n_samples, n_sites, min_per_group, destrand, use_db, db_path` (`write_tsv`).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/unite_stats.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: unite_stats.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_6Nuh111TwZBlXlGRfoSrgByN", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit library in R.\\n2. Use methylKit::methRead to read the bismark coverage files with the specified parameters.\\n3. Use methylKit::unite to unite the methylation data.\\n4. Save the united methylBase object using saveRDS.\\n5. Write the unite statistics to a TSV file.\\n6. Check if the output file unite_stats.tsv exists.\\n7. Submit the task as done if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (379 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_6Nuh111TwZBlXlGRfoSrgByN"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_zgdAC6yhsjLL69aj3DqsWyGY", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Read the bismark coverage files\\nfile.list <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleC.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleD.bismark.cov')\\ntreatment <- c(0, 0, 1, 1)\\nmk_raw <- methRead(file.list, pipeline='bismarkCoverage', mincov=4, treatment=treatment, assembly='mock_v1')\\n\\n# Unite the methylation data\\nmk_united <- unite(mk_raw, min.per.group=1, destrand=FALSE)\\n\\n# Save the united methylBase object\\nsaveRDS(mk_united, 'output/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Write unite statistics to a TSV file\\nunite_stats <- data.frame(n_samples=length(mk_united@sample.ids),\\n                          n_sites=length(mk_united@sites),\\n                          min_per_group=1,\\n                          destrand=FALSE,\\n                          use_db=FALS